  "text": "Structural studies suggest that AIM motifs adopt an extended b-conformation and form an intermolecular parallel b-sheet with the b2 domain of ATG8 family proteins [CITATION_1] . It is possible that the consensus W/YxxL/V/I could be recognized in both orientations in the primary sequence. We showed that mutating the hydrophobic residues possibly required for ATG8 binding resulted in inhibition of At-TSPO degradation. We cannot exclude the possibility that a fraction of At-TSPO might be degraded by other cellular process than autophagy. However, genetic and pharmacological inhibition of the proteasome pathway did not affect the stability of At-TSPO, and the autophagydependent degradation pathway was conserved even after heterologous expression of At-TSPO in yeast. These findings suggest that the cellular mechanism for At-TSPO recognition and degradation by eukaryotic cells is a housekeeping mechanism. It would be interesting to determine whether any of the degradation-deficient mutant forms of At-TSPO has a phenotypic consequence in the plant.",
